        <num>CC 1941</num>
        <heading>1941.  Notice of commencement of performance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1941.  Notice of commencement of performance
When commencement of the performance either constitutes acceptance or makes the offer irrevocable, the offeree must give prompt notice of that commencement unless the offeror knows or should know that the offeree has begun to perform.  An offeree who fails to give the notice is liable for damages.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
